div1.p:
I am gardener at this house: in the night the house was broke open, I was brewing;
Betty Oldfield
came to me in the morning in the brewhouse, and asked me whether I had been in the house, I told her I had not; she immediately said, then the house is broke open; I did not take much notice of what she said at that time, but a little after she insisted upon my going in with her; this was between six and seven o'clock.
